                </button>
                
                <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" role="presentation" class="icon icon--wide icon-chevron-down" viewbox="0 0 498.98 284.49"><defs></defs><path class="cls-1" d="M80.93 271.76A35 35 0 0 1 140.68 247l189.74 189.75L520.16 247a35 35 0 1 1 49.5 49.5L355.17 511a35 35 0 0 1-49.5 0L91.18 296.5a34.89 34.89 0 0 1-10.25-24.74z" transform="translate(-80.93 -236.76)"></path></svg>
            </div>
            <div id="1569828417275" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading-1569828417275" data-parent="#accordion">
                <div class="card-body">
                    
                    <p>
Wonderchef Regalia Coffee Grinder is the perfect appliance to give you fresh coffee powder for all kinds of
machines you may have at home or work. The size of the grounds can be customized depending on your
brewing method and personal preference, starting from the coarse ground of French Press or pour-over to
the finer grounds used in brew and 5-bar machine to the finest ones for 15 and 19-bar machines.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    
        <div class="card card-2">
            <div class="card-header" id="heading-1569828878550">
                <button class="title collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#1569828878550" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="1569828878550">
Why coffee grinding is better than buying pre-ground coffee?
                </button>
                
                <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" role="presentation" class="icon icon--wide icon-chevron-down" viewbox="0 0 498.98 284.49"><defs></defs><path class="cls-1" d="M80.93 271.76A35 35 0 0 1 140.68 247l189.74 189.75L520.16 247a35 35 0 1 1 49.5 49.5L355.17 511a35 35 0 0 1-49.5 0L91.18 296.5a34.89 34.89 0 0 1-10.25-24.74z" transform="translate(-80.93 -236.76)"></path></svg>
            </div>
            <div id="1569828878550" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading-1569828878550" data-parent="#accordion">
                <div class="card-body">
                    
                    <p>
Whole coffee beans preserve their natural flavour and they produce fresh powder or ground which is rich
in taste and aroma. Coffee made from such ground is richer, accentuating your coffee experience. 
Pre-ground coffee, on the other hand, loses the richness of flavour and aroma quickly with interaction with
air, humidity and sunlight. Hence freshly ground coffee is always a preferred option.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    
        <div class="card card-2">
            <div class="card-header" id="heading-1569828968822">
                <button class="title collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#1569828968822" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="1569828968822">
What is a Burr Grinder?
                </button>
                
                <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" role="presentation" class="icon icon--wide icon-chevron-down" viewbox="0 0 498.98 284.49"><defs></defs><path class="cls-1" d="M80.93 271.76A35 35 0 0 1 140.68 247l189.74 189.75L520.16 247a35 35 0 1 1 49.5 49.5L355.17 511a35 35 0 0 1-49.5 0L91.18 296.5a34.89 34.89 0 0 1-10.25-24.74z" transform="translate(-80.93 -236.76)"></path></svg>
            </div>
            <div id="1569828968822" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading-1569828968822" data-parent="#accordion">
                <div class="card-body">
                    
                    <p>
A burr is a grinding wheel that crushes the beans to a uniform size as per the setting you choose. A uniform
size is essential for creating an awesome coffee experience. There are two different burr grinders, conical
or flat plate. Wonderchef Regalia Coffee Grinder uses a conical burr for maximum efficiency. It is better
than simply crushing the beans in a high-speed mixer-grinder with blades as that causes oxidation and loss
of taste. Moreover one cannot control the size of the grounds in a normal mixer.
</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    
        <div class="card card-2">
            <div class="card-header" id="heading-1569829479298">
                <button class="title collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#1569829479298" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="1569829479298">
Why there are so many grind options in the machine? Why coffee ground size is so important?
                </button>
                
                <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" role="presentation" class="icon icon--wide icon-chevron-down" viewbox="0 0 498.98 284.49"><defs></defs><path class="cls-1" d="M80.93 271.76A35 35 0 0 1 140.68 247l189.74 189.75L520.16 247a35 35 0 1 1 49.5 49.5L355.17 511a35 35 0 0 1-49.5 0L91.18 296.5a34.89 34.89 0 0 1-10.25-24.74z" transform="translate(-80.93 -236.76)"></path></svg>
            </div>
            <div id="1569829479298" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading-1569829479298" data-parent="#accordion">
                <div class="card-body">
                    
                    <p>
Based on the choice of the machine, grind-size affects the flavour and texture of the coffee. It makes all the
difference between a flavourful coffee and a tasteless, bland or overly bitter one. A coarse grind is best for
a French Press brewer, with a sea salt texture. Cold brew works best with an extra coarse grind size
mirroring peppercorns. Medium ground size works best for pour-over coffees and espresso tastes best in
finely ground coffee beans. And superfine coffee grounds are often used for Turkish coffee. Wonderchef
coffee grinder gives you all choices.
                  </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    
